---
const highlights = [
  "Established 2014 in the Triangle area",
  "Specialized in small business & professional services",
  "Certified advisors with industry credentials",
  "Client-first, transparent approach",
];
---

<section class="bg-slate-50 py-16">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[color:var(--color-primary)] mb-6">
          About Summit Edge Advisory
        </h2>
        <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 mb-4">
            We founded Summit Edge Advisory on a simple belief: every business owner and professional deserves access to strategic guidance without the complexity or inflated fees of traditional firms.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
            Our team combines decades of experience across finance, real estate, operations, and consulting. We've helped hundreds of clients in the Raleigh-Durham area navigate critical decisions—from launching new ventures to optimizing existing operations.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            What sets us apart is our commitment to clarity and collaboration. We don't just hand you a report—we work alongside you, ensuring you understand every recommendation and feel confident in every choice.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-card p-8 shadow-card">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[color:var(--color-primary)] mb-6">
          Why Choose Us
        </h3>
        <ul class="space-y-4">
          {highlights.map((item) => (
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[color:var(--color-secondary)] mr-3 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-slate-700">{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
